    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Why do most prenatal gummies not contain iron?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Most prenatal gummies exclude iron for three reasons. First, iron has a strong metallic taste that is extremely difficult to mask in a gummy format — it can make the entire product unpalatable, which defeats the purpose of choosing a gummy for compliance. Second, iron reacts with other vitamins and minerals in the gummy matrix, potentially degrading vitamin C, folate, and other nutrients over time. Third, iron can cause the gummy texture to become gritty or discolored. These formulation challenges have led approximately 90% of prenatal gummy brands to exclude iron entirely, making iron-containing prenatal gummies a rare and valuable find.' },
