      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The recommended daily iron intake during pregnancy is 27mg according to the NIH. However, many prenatal gummies that contain iron provide only 9-18mg — a meaningful contribution but not the full daily requirement. If your prenatal gummy provides less than 27mg, you can supplement with dietary iron from red meat (2.6mg per 3oz serving), fortified cereals (18mg per serving), lentils (3.3mg per half cup), and spinach (3.2mg per half cup). Women with documented iron deficiency or anemia may require 60-120mg of supplemental iron daily under physician supervision. Always confirm your iron needs with your OB/GYN through routine blood work.' },
    },
