      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can I take an iron gummy separately from my prenatal?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes, and this is actually the most common approach for pregnant women who take gummy prenatals. Since most prenatal gummies exclude iron, pairing a prenatal gummy with a separate iron gummy supplement is a practical workaround. Take the iron gummy at a different time than your prenatal — ideally 2 hours apart — because calcium, zinc, and other minerals in the prenatal can compete with iron for absorption. Take iron with vitamin C (orange juice, strawberries) to enhance absorption, and avoid taking it with dairy, coffee, or tea, which inhibit iron absorption. See our Best Iron Gummies for Anemia guide for standalone options.' },
