    </div>

    <p>The World Health Organization estimates that 40% of pregnant women worldwide are anemic, with iron deficiency as the primary cause. Iron deficiency anemia during pregnancy is not a minor inconvenience — it is associated with a 2.5x increased risk of preterm birth, significantly higher rates of low birth weight, elevated risk of postpartum depression, and impaired infant cognitive development that can persist into childhood. Finding a prenatal gummy that actually contains iron is not a preference — it is a clinical priority.</p>

